http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html
You’ll get an interactive UI that lists all the endpoints you just coded – great for quick manual testing and for the “tested through Swagger” part of the rubric.

9️⃣ Quick checklist to verify you meet every project requirement
Requirement	How you satisfy it
JPA persistence layer	Entities annotated with @Entity; repositories extend JpaRepository.
All CRUD on a table	Controllers expose POST/GET/PUT/DELETE for Artist, Album, Genre.
CRUD on join table	POST /albums/{a}/genres/{g} → INSERT, DELETE … → DELETE rows in album_genre.
≥ 3 entities / tables	Artist, Album, Genre (join table is auto‑generated).
One‑to‑many	Artist → Album (@OneToMany).
Many‑to‑many	Album ↔ Genre (@ManyToMany with album_genre).
All 4 CRUD ops on at least one entity	All three entities have full CRUD endpoints.
REST API	@RestController with JSON payloads.
Testable via Swagger/Postman	Swagger UI added (optional) + Postman examples provided.
Use Spring JPA	spring-boot-starter-data-jpa in pom, JpaRepository usage.
